Spray cold grill and utensils well with cooking spray. Position grill 3 to 4 inches from heat. Heat grill according to manufacturer's suggestion. Heat jelly and garlic in small saucepan over medium heat until jelly melts. Or, heat in microwave oven in microwave-safe bowl on HIGH (100% power) 1 minute, or until melted. Stir in cilantro. Reserve 1/4 cup jelly mixture to serve with cooked ham steak. Place ham steak on cook grate over medium heat. Grill 3 minutes. Turn ham steak over; brush with half of remaining jelly mixture and continue grilling 3 minutes. Turn ham steak again; brush with remaining jelly mixture. Continue to grill 2 minutes. Serve with reserved jelly mixture.